N/AParks Canada AgencyKejimkujik National Park and National Historic SiteContains Covid AlertThere are many sides to Kejimkujik National Park and National Historic Site. Inland, old growth hemlock, sugar maple and yellow aspen trees border warm-water lakes with quartzite shores. Kejimkujik Seaside, a separate landscape, juxtaposes with colourful barrens, granite cobbles and white-sand beaches. The land also tells the tale of the Mi’kmaw, carved in stone and illuminated through story and legend.
